# src/

This directory contains the implementation source files for the Helix Project, organized by component. Each subfolder corresponds to a major component of the language and contains the actual code (implementations) for that component.

As you add more components, update this README to reflect the new structure and their purposes.

## Subfolders

### lexer/
Contains the implementation files for the lexical analysis component.  
These files handle tokenizing source code, processing character streams, and managing token types.

### parser/
Contains the implementation files for the parsing component.  
These files handle syntactic analysis, grammar rules, and building parse trees from token streams.

### ast/
Contains the implementation files for the Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) component.  
These files handle representing, traversing, and manipulating the AST for further analysis and code generation.

### types/
Contains the implementation files for type definitions and file system utilities.  
This includes code for file handling, path manipulation, and other type-related utilities used throughout the project.

